    • Method Detail

      • getInitialBmsMaxEverChargeCurrent

        int getInitialBmsMaxEverChargeCurrent()
        Defines the (estimated) maximum expected Charge current.

        This is used as a reference for percentage values in Voltage-To-Percent and Temperature-To-Percent definitions. If during runtime a higher value is provided, that one is taken from then on.

        Returns:
        the (estimated) maximum expected Charge current in [A]

      • getInitialBmsMaxEverDischargeCurrent

        Returns:
        the (estimated) maximum expected Charge current in [A]
